  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bangin-haddock-balti/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bangin-haddock-balti/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Dice your<strong> tomato[es]</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bangin-haddock-balti/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[140ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[180ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bangin-haddock-balti/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> ginger</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 2 min</p><p>Add your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground paprika</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bangin-haddock-balti/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>diced tomatoes</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the tomatoes have started to break down</p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> and cook for an initial 5-6 min or until the sauce is beginning to thicken</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bangin-haddock-balti/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>haddock bites </strong>dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p><p>Add the <strong>haddock bites </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for a further 4-5 min or until cooked through – this is your <strong>fragrant haddock balti</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bangin-haddock-balti/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>fragrant haddock balti</strong> with the <strong>brown rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
